lence, constitutional conflict and political party disagreements. In addition, a comparison is drawn between direct rule and devolution, analysing both the positive and negative impact of direct rule, as well as identifying where there has been minimal divergence in processes and outcomes. It will prove an invaluable reference source on direct rule and provide a comparative basis for assessing devolution for students of public administration, government, politics, public policy and devolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCentral-local government relationszNorthern Ireland. 0aDecentralization in governmentzNorthern Ireland. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aNorthern Ireland.  aWestminster parliament.  acivil service.  across-border structures.  adirect rule.  alocal government.  aombudsmen offices.  apublic expenditure process.  aquangos.  asystem of governance.1 aBirrell, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779271640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847792716423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847792716/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles